{"title": "Amateur Cracksman", "description": "<i>\"I'd tasted blood, and it was all over with me. Why should I work when I could steal? Why settle down to some humdrum uncongenial billet, when excitement, romance, danger and a decent living were all going begging together?\"- A. J. Raffles, The Ides of March.</i><br /><br />The Amateur Cracksman is the first collection of stories about A. J. Raffles, gentleman, cricketer, and thief. After stopping his old school friend, Bunny Manders, from a desperate attempt at suicide, Raffles introduces the unsuspecting Bunny to a new way of earning a living, burglary. Though frequently horrified by Raffles's actions, the conscience-stricken Bunny stands by him through all their adventures, firm to his promise, \"When you want me, I'm your man!\" (Summary by Kristin Hughes)", "duration": 19524, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1096", "name": "E. W. Hornung"}], "coverArt": "http://archive.org/download/amateur_cracksman_librivox/Amateur_Cracksman_1004.jpg", "copyright_year": "1899", "genres": ["Crime & Mystery Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Kristin Hughes"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Kristin Hughes"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Kara Shallenberg"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Ides of March", "readers": [28], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/amateur_cracksman_librivox/amateur_cracksman_01_hornung_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2919}, {"section": 2, "title": "A Costume Piece", "readers": [28], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/amateur_cracksman_librivox/amateur_cracksman_02_hornung_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2170}, {"section": 3, "title": "Gentlemen and Players", "readers": [28], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/amateur_cracksman_librivox/amateur_cracksman_03_hornung_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2509}, {"section": 4, "title": "Le Premier Pas", "readers": [28], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/amateur_cracksman_librivox/amateur_cracksman_04_hornung_64